Students protesting against the University Grants Commissionâ€™s (UGC) decision to scrap non-NET fellowship are going to start a nationwide campaign from Monday. A nationwide signature campaign is slated to start from January 18 and will go on till February 15. The students are demanding an increase in the amount of non-NET fellowship and expansion of the non-NET scheme to State universities without any exclusionary criteria for all research scholars.By the end of the campaign, the signatures will be submitted to the Union Human Resource Development Ministry, the President and the Prime Minister. The campaign will also run online to ensure maximum participation.